2nd) position a warrior and paladin and shadowknight at the corner between the two rows of stairs near the door where Grieg is.<br>
3rd) Puller pulls Grieg out of the room down the stairs, SK then whacks him with HT and dies to position him.  Hell add in a sacarficial chanter to die and do a tash on him as well to keep him in the corner.<br>
4th) Have Warrior start whacking Grieg to get argo, when warrior gets low, Paladin LOH's and dies.  Don't have anyone start healing or debuffing till warrior has got argo.<br>
5th) Do a few spam heals on the warrior and then start debuffing.<br>
6th) LOH rotation and all melees engage.<br>
7th) sit back and kill grieg and then his 1hp corporeal version and enjoy some loot.<br>
<br>
Its about that easy.  And a warrior can maintain argo as long as he's given time to build it up.  Griegs AE is for all extents and purposes unresistable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufendrylistalindir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fendryl Istalindir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 9:28:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11665.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: song</span><hr size=1> 4.5) pray that people don't get pushed through the geometry &amp; ported out to Scarlet Desert.<br>
